{meta: title Empty Arms And A Heart Full Of Sorrow}
{meta: artist Hawkshaw Hawkins}
{meta: composer Wally Fowler and Graydon Hall}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[C]With empty arms a [F]heart full of [C]sorrow
[G7]I sit alone in the pale moonlight
[C]Alone [F]where we were once [C]together
[G7]And I wonder where you are [C]tonight
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[F]These empty arms were once around [C]you
[G7]They held you close to a happy heart
[C]Yes close to [F]a heart that now is [C]aching
[G7]And aching because we're now [C]apart
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[F]With empty arms and a heart full of [C]sorrow
[G7]I sit alone and I wish for you
[C]I wonder [F]dear if you are [C]lonely
[G7]And if your arms are empty [C]too
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 4}
[F]Without your love life is not worth [C]living
[G7]I dread the years I will have to pay
[C]Please darling [F]come back and make me [C]happy
[G7]There's no one on earth can take your [C]place
{end_of_verse}

